<usermanual>
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	

							FIVE FACTOR MODEL RATING FORM (FFMRF)
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	

Script Author: Katja Borchert, Ph.D. (katjab@millisecond.com) for Millisecond Software, LLC
Date: 01-08-2014
last updated:  02-22-2022 by K. Borchert (katjab@millisecond.com) for Millisecond Software, LLC

Script Copyright © 02-22-2022 Millisecond Software

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
BACKGROUND INFO 	
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
This script implements the Five Factor Model Rating Form (FFMRF) as described in:

Mullins-Sweatt, S.N, Jamerson, J.E., Samuel, D.B., Olson. D.R., & Thomas A. Widiger, T.A. (2006).
Psychometric Properties of an Abbreviated Instrument of the Five-Factor Model. Assessment, 13, 119-137.

This script is based on a paper and pencil scoring form genereously shared by Dr. Samuel. 
Millisecond Software thanks Dr. Samuel for his assistance with writing this script!

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
OVERVIEW
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
The FFMRF contains 6 5-choice Likert questions for each of the 5 personality factors:
neuroticism (N), extraversion (E), openness (O), agreeableness (A), conscientiousness (C).
The 30 questions are spread over 5 surveypages (one page per factor).

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
DURATION 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
the default set-up of the script takes appr. 2 minutes to complete

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
DATA FILE INFORMATION 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
The default data stored in the data files are:

(1) Raw data file: 'fivefactormodel.iqdat' 

date, time:						date and time script was run with the current group/subjectnumber 
subject, group, session:	  	with the current subject/groupnumber/session id
build:							the Inquisit build 

q*_response:					response given (in assigned values)
									Scale: 1 (extremely low) - 5 (extremely high)
									no reversed scored questions
									
q*_latency:						how much time (in ms) the participant spent on the surveypage with this particular 
								question (the last time this particular surveypage was visited)

(2) Summary data file: 'fivefactormodel_summary*.iqdat'

inquisit.version: 					Inquisit version run
computer.platform:				the platform the script was run on (win/mac/ios/android)
startDate:						date script was run
startTime:						time script was started
subjectid:						assigned subject id number
groupid:						assigned group id number
sessionid:						assigned session id number
elapsedTime:					time it took to run script (in ms); measured from onset to offset of script
completed:						0 = script was not completed (prematurely aborted); 
								1 = script was completed (all conditions run)

neuroticism - 
conscientiousness: 				the scores for the 5 factors

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
EDITABLE CODE 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
check below for (relatively) easily editable parameters, stimuli, instructions etc. 
Keep in mind that you can use this script as a template and therefore always "mess" with the entire code 
to further customize your experiment.

The parameters you can change are:

/completeinstructions:			the complete instructions that appear at the top of the first surveypage
/repeatinstructions:			the instructions that appear on each subsequent page

/responselegend:				the response legend
</usermanual>


**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
	EDITABLE PARAMETERS: change editable parameters here
**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************

<parameters>
/completeinstructions = "Please describe yourself on a 1 to 5 scale on each of the following 30 personality traits, where 1 is extremely low (i.e., extremely lower than the average person), 2 is low, 3 is neither high nor low (i.e., does not differ from the average person), 4 is high and 5 is extremely high.  Use any number from 1 to 5. Please provide a rating for all 30 traits.

For example: on the first trait (anxiousness), a score of 1 would indicate that you think you are extremely low in anxiousness (i.e., relaxed, unconcerned, cool).  A score of 2 would indicate that you think you are low in anxiousness (lower than the average person, but not extremely low). A score of 5 would indicate that you think you are extremely high in anxiousness (i.e., fearful, apprehensive); a score of 4 would indicate you think you are higher than the average person in anxiousness, but not extremely high.  A score of 3 would indicate that you think you are neither high nor low in anxiousness (does not differ from the average person) or that you are unable to decide. <%expressions.buttoninstruct1%> the number that applies to you for each of the traits."

/repeatinstructions = "<%expressions.buttoninstruct1%> the number that applies to you for each of the traits.
"

/responselegend = "5= Extremely high  4= High  3= Neither high nor low  2= Low  1=Extremely Low
"
</parameters>



****************************************************************************************************
general instruction expressions: adjust the instruction text depending on device used to run script
****************************************************************************************************
<expressions>
/buttoninstruct1 = if (computer.touch && !computer.hasKeyboard) {"Touch";} else {"Click";}
</expressions>


**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
	EDITABLE INSTRUCTIONS: change instructions here
**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
<instruct>
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 3.00%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
</instruct>

<page End>
Thank you!
</page>

**************************************************************************************************************
								!!!REMAINING CODE: Customize after careful consideration only!!!
**************************************************************************************************************

**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
	DEFAULTS
**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
script requires Inquisit 6.5.2.0 or higher

<defaults>
/canvasaspectratio = (4,3)
/minimumversion = "6.5.2.0"
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 3%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/txbgcolor = white
/ txcolor = black
/ quitcommand = (Alt+18)
</defaults>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	DATA: this section contains data file information
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************

********************
raw data: FFMRF.iqx
********************

********************
Summary data
********************

<summarydata>
/columns = (inquisit.version, computer.platform,script.startDate, script.startTime, 
script.subjectId, script.groupId, script.sessionId, script.elapsedTime, 
script.completed,
expressions.neuroticism, expressions.extraversion, expressions.openness, expressions.agreeableness, expressions.conscientiousness)
</summarydata>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	EXPRESSIONS
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
/Neuroticism - 
/Conscientiousness: 			the scores for the 5 factors

<expressions>
/Neuroticism = radiobuttons.N_Anxiousness.response + radiobuttons.N_Hostility.response + radiobuttons.N_Depressiveness.response +
radiobuttons.N_SelfConsciousness.response + radiobuttons.N_Impulsivity.response + radiobuttons.N_Vulnerability.response

/Extraversion = radiobuttons.E_Warmth.response + radiobuttons.E_Gregariousness.response + radiobuttons.E_Assertiveness.response +
radiobuttons.E_Activity.response + radiobuttons.E_ExcSeeking.response + radiobuttons.E_PosEmotion.response

/Openness = radiobuttons.O_Fantasy.response + radiobuttons.O_Aesthetics.response + radiobuttons.O_Feelings.response +
radiobuttons.O_Actions.response + radiobuttons.O_Ideas.response + radiobuttons.O_Values.response

/Agreeableness = radiobuttons.A_Trust.response + radiobuttons.A_StraightForward.response + radiobuttons.A_Altruism.response +
radiobuttons.A_Compliance.response + radiobuttons.A_Modesty.response + radiobuttons.A_TenderMindedness.response

/Conscientiousness = radiobuttons.C_Competence.response + radiobuttons.C_Order.response + radiobuttons.C_Dutifulness.response +
radiobuttons.C_Achievement.response + radiobuttons.C_SelfDiscipline.response + radiobuttons.C_Deliberation.response

</expressions>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	QUESTIONS
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
Note: by default all questions are required to be answered. To change
/required = false

